column2: This plugin is used to fix elements on the page (top, bottom, anywhere); however, it still allows the element to continue to move left or right with the horizontal scroll.

See #22: Added a minWidth option that will deactivate the plugin if the window does not meet a minimum width.  Once the window exceeds the minimum width, the plugin will reactivate.

See #20: Refined the fix to not fire the unfix event constantly if the original position is anything by fixed.

See #20: Added a reset flag to the checkScroll function to determine when a window resize had taken place.  Check was reset in each of the non-footer use cases.  This corrects the issue seen where the target element stopped being fixed, after a window resize, when the target's limit was active.
